  "body": "We have a recommend way to use setState: use a function instead of object.\r\n```\r\nthis.setState(prevState => ({\r\n  a: prevState.a + 1\r\n}))\r\n```\r\nBut we have an async functions. And we cannot push him inside setState.\r\nCan you add an `(State, Props) => Promise` arg?\r\nNow, we write this:\r\n```\r\nasync foo = async () => {\r\n  const state = await Promise.resolve(this.state)\r\n  const data = await doSmth(state)\r\n  this.setState({data})\r\n}\r\n```\r\ninstead of\r\n```\r\nfoo = () => this.setState(async prevState => ({\r\n  data: await doSmth(prevState)\r\n}))\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
